OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1775826669
OL,3,CThird day of fuel price protests bring
OL,4,CDublin to a standstill
OL,6,FHe said "enormous effort" had gone
OL,7,Finto maintaining fuel supplies to
OL,8,FIreland since the outbreak of the war
OL,9,Fin Iran and it is "profoundly
OL,10,Fdisappointing" people are being
OL,11,Fprevented from accessing fuel.
OL,13,FHealth Minister Jennifer Carroll
OL,14,FMacNeill and Health Service Executive
OL,15,Fchief executive Anne O'Connor have
OL,16,Fjointly called for all approaches to
OL,17,Fmedical facilities to be kept clear
OL,18,Fduring the protests.
OL,26,@nD@IOUnD@YO]qD@SOUrD@NO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/17
